-- S.Korean shares pare losses on improved China PMIs, won down
-- 
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 02:20AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, Sept 3 (Reuters) - South Korean shares ended flat on Wednesday, recovering most of their morning losses thanks to a strong performance in regional markets and on surveys showing improved services sector activity in China. [ID:nL3N0R40EO]

The Korea Composite Stock Price Index (KOSPI) <.KS11> ease  0.02 percent lower to 2,051.2 points, rebounding from earlier losses which saw the index hit a 3-week low. The South Korean won <KRW=> edged lower against the dollar, which rose to a 14-month high against a basket of major currencies. The won found some support on dollar-selling by exporters ahead of a long holiday weekend.